---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Infinity: Mercenaries"
  description="A narrative mercenary campaign framework for Infinity N5."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <img
      class="hero-image"
      src="/images/hero-operations.png"
      alt="A sci-fi mercenary team planning around a holographic mission table."
    />
    <div class="hero-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Unofficial Infinity N5 campaign framework</p>
      <h1>Infinity: Mercenaries</h1>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        Build a persistent mercenary company, take dangerous contracts, and watch
        your operators earn scars, reputation, credits, and enemies across a season.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/rules/">Read the Rules</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/contracts/">Browse Contracts</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section intro-grid" aria-labelledby="field-manual">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Field manual</p>
      <h2 id="field-manual">Small battles. Long consequences.</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
      Mercenaries turns Infinity into a compact campaign experience built around
      4-7 unit strike teams, persistent progression, downtime choices, and mission
      variety. The rules are designed for narrative pressure without losing the
      sharp tactical feel of the base game.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-band" id="campaign" aria-label="Campaign pillars">
    <article>
      <span class="kicker">01</span>
      <h3>Companies</h3>
      <p>Recruit from chosen sectorials, appoint a captain, track credits, and shape a roster over time.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="kicker">02</span>
      <h3>Contracts</h3>
      <p>Play focused missions with custom objectives, twists, deployment rules, and narrative stakes.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="kicker">03</span>
      <h3>Progression</h3>
      <p>Earn XP, suffer injuries, buy equipment, and make downtime decisions between engagements.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="kicker">04</span>
      <h3>Balance Pressure</h3>
      <p>Inducements and elite deployment help underdogs stay dangerous without flattening company identity.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section split" id="resources">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Rules-first website</p>
      <h2>Built to evolve with the campaign.</h2>
      <p>
        The new site stores rules as Markdown content, making it easier to revise
        wording, reorganize sections, generate references, and collaborate with AI
        while keeping the public reading experience polished on desktop and mobile.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="terminal-panel" aria-label="Site structure preview">
      <p>/rules/company-creation</p>
      <p>/rules/campaign-seasons</p>
      <p>/rules/experience</p>
      <p>/contracts/extraction</p>
      <p>/contracts/titan</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
